The paper discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) to address challenges faced by VPN service providers, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of a logically centralized controller for network devices, which is a key aspect of SDN (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the management complexity and scalability issues faced by service providers, which could fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and information theory (cs.IT).
